Linux commands 

q1 : Find hidden file name in directory , 

use find . -name ".*" -f ( every hidden file starts with .) and -f to find for only files 

cat .hiddenfile to view content of it 

pwd : current working directory 

ls /mnt/ : this shows all the drive mounted in my system

touch name.txt : to create a txt file

nano name.txt : to write to that file 

Ctrl-X to exit (save and discard) the nano. 

cat name.txt : to view the information 
